      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC46e6b3b02afd100587d28d91941052d2"></a>Refitting the rear brake control
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4347"> </a>If removed, apply recommended threadlocker to screw (17), install brake cylinder control rod (18) with spacer (19) and tighten
            screw (17) to 10 Nm ±10%.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4349"> </a>Make sure that the adjustment screw (20) and nut (21) setting is the specified one.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4351"> </a>Apply grease on the internal surface of the bush (10) and threadlocker on the pin (6).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4353"> </a>Install O-ring (11) onto pin (6).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4355"> </a>Insert pin (6) on brake control lever (7), fit the other O-ring (11) and washer (9).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_005603170.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_006103171.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_005703172.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4364"> </a>Reconnect the hose (14), locating the sealing washers (15) on both sides of the union, and secure it with the special screw
            (12) and hose (16) securing it with the hose clip (13).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4366"> </a>Tighten the special screw (12) to a torque of 23 Nm ±10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_005803173.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="Attenzione"><img class="Attenzione" width="28" height="25" style="display: inline; float: none; left: 0.0; text-align: left; top: 0.0;" src="img/note.jpg">Note
      </div>
      <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4371"> </a>Pay special attention to hose orientation on rear brake cylinder.
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_041704544.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4376"> </a>Apply recommended threadlocker on pin (6).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4378"> </a>Install brake control lever (7) with spring (8), and start pin (6) in its hole.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4380"> </a>Position the end (A) of spring (8) as shown.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4382"> </a>Tighten pin (6) to a torque of 23 Nm ±10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_006203175.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4388"> </a>Refit the rear brake (1) fixing bracket (5) on rear brake control (7).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_005103156.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4393"> </a>Apply the recommended threadlocker on the screws (2).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4395"> </a>Position the rear brake master cylinder (3) on the vehicle and insert the fixing screws (2).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4397"> </a>Insert the rod (4) inside the master cylinder (3), after applying the recommended grease.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4399"> </a>Tighten the screws (2) to a torque of 10 Nm ±10%.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_006303176.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4404"> </a>Connect rear stop switch (1) to main wiring.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_004903153.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4409"> </a>For position of hoses (14) and (16) and hose clips, comply with the provisions under Section "<a href="78699.html#DUC690d85c02b1310058c6793c8b30eb8d2">Routing wiring harnesses / hoses</a>" for the base version or under Section "<a href="78701.html#DUCba4d95002b1410058c6b93c8b30eb8d2">Routing wiring harnesses / hoses</a>" for the Pikes Peak, Granturismo or Touring versions.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e4418"> </a>Fill the rear braking system (<a href="77261.html#DUC957e61d829fb1005804484b414d9e1d2">Changing the rear brake system fluid</a>).
         </div>
      </div>
